    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-09-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-09-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="265" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d265">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hices</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Lima Peru</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-09-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 2,
                                    1892</hi>
                        </date>. (Received September 29.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 421.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to Mr. Neill’s No. 407, of July
                            27, 1892, and my Nos. 355, of April 1, and 357, of April 8, 1892, I have
                            to say that in view of the action of the representatives of England,
                            France, Germany, Spain, and Italy, in jointly urging upon the Peruvian
                            Government the necessity of paying the just claims of citizens of those
                            Governments, I deemed it best once more to call the attention of the
                            Government to the claims known as that of the Hydrographic
                            Commission.</p>
                <p>Accordingly, on this date I forwarded to the minister of foreign affairs
                            a note on the subject, and I inclose herewith a copy of the same.</p>
                <p>In expressing the hope that something may come of it I can not refrain
                            also from saying that I have but little confidence that it will be
                            immediately paid. The Peruvian Government is not paying any of its
                            creditors, as I have heretofore explained.</p>
                <p>Your, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hicks.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
